rComments: This is one of the best professors in the faculty of Health Science. Professor Phillips made the transition to online learning very manageable given this is a heavy course. The grading criteria was very straightforward, overall easy to do well in her class if you attend class.

Karen Phillips is a GEM! I was worried because of her reviews, but she was so caring, sweet, and kind and truly cares about students. Her exams were 100% fair with no textbook or readings required. This course is heavy and requires a lot of study time, but her evaluations were very straightforward. Turned out to be my fav class of the semester :)

Professor Philips was a wonderful instructor even during stressful times. Her powerpoint recordings are very straightforward and she will only test you on material from her slides (no readings at all). There IS a lot of work for this course but this is due to the course being heavy itself and not her giving unnecessary work. No effort  low grade
Amazing professor. Was accessible outside of class for questions, made lectures interesting, the tests were based on what she taught and she marked fairly

Ok so I read these reviews before taking her class this semester and I was pretty worried. Having gone through the course she is the sweetest lady. Obviously this course isn't a walk in the park, there is a lot to learn, but she teaches it as simply as possible and it's very easy to follow along with the lectures. The tests are super fair too!

Arguably my worst prof. Extremely inconsiderate for students. Her powerpoint recordings went on for like 3-4 hours sometimes and definitely 2+ hours on average when she is only supposed to talk for 80 minutes. The teaching in the recordings are is unclear and messy. On top of all that, she gives almost no time for students to write her midterms.
Karen makes HSS 3305 enjoyable, as she explains topics really well! Her exams are tough, as you need to know almost everything from the lectures, but she is fair.

No, no, just no. I switched out of my whole program simply because of this one class. AVOID HER, EVERY OTHER PERSON WHO TOOK IT WITH ANOTHER PROF HAD A FAR BETTER EXPERIENCE. SAVE YOURSELF FROM THIS TORTURE.
I pray for ya'll if you want to remain someone sane by the end of your undergraduate I would avoid this prof at all cost trust, any other prof is better.

Ladies and gentlemen I have taken, physics, biochemistry, orgo chem and nothing can compare to this class. I am telling you better to take it with another prof the following semeter I have had a 9 cgpa the entire way through and took her class and now my gpa is disgusting.

Take Patho with her 100%. Exams are tricky as in you need to know your stuff but so fair, all her questions are clear and directly from slides. The paper is pretty easy and she bumps you up if you go see her! Her lectures are super interesting and makes you look forward to class! Patho is just a lot of material but if you put in work can get an A

This is a hard class and theres a lot of content so you cant get away with only studying a few days before the exam. But professor Phillips is one of the best profs at the University. Take this class with her, work hard, and youll easily get that A+.

The assignment is the only thing that saves your grade. the exams are brutal because its so much content (shes usually testing you on 10 lectures at a time). The multiple choice is really tricky in the format of A, B , C, A and B, B and C or none of the above. The final had open ended questions and fill in the blanks, KNOW YOUR EXAMPLES
She used the word "OBR" for leptin receptors instead of making our lives easy and saying Lep-R. AVOID AT ALL COSTS

Karen is willing to answer questions regarding the course after class and during office hours. Lectures are very straight forward, studying ppts is enough to do well on tests. But the paper's marking scheme is unknown, you either do really badly or get 100. Exams are mcq with a, b, c, a and b, b and c, very tricky. Take patho with any other prof.

Decent professor but she is quite robotic in her lecturing. Assignment was interesting but was so much work and was only worth 20%. Midterm was fair but final was tricky. Super nice woman though and very approachable and you definitely do not need to buy the textbook

Phillips is so organized! She is extremely clear of exactly she wants from you. She expects a lot but is very clear about what that is. Her lectures are good for understanding the material in general but the rest of the details are up to you to understand and go through. She is also super helpful and approachable.
Amazing Professor! Conveys subject matter exceptionally well but MCQ is very tricky. Heavy course load so start studying from day 1.
Great professor. Her multiple choice can be tricky, especially if you didn't study. For patho, you don't need the textbook just be very attentive to her slides on small details.

If you can take this course with another prof, go for it! Or take it with her if you wanna drop your GPA. Midterm and final is very tricky and unfair!! She is very nice when you approach her after class and will take the time to answer your questions. However, she will  not reply to your e-mail if you ask to see her outside classroom.

Great lecturer! but I found her midterm  multiple choice questions to be brutal. There's 5 options for every question and 2 of them are always " a and b" or "a and c" so this will trick you even if you know your material.I also thought it wasn't fair at all how the other section's midterm average was 12-15% + higher than ours.. kind of discouraging

I'm about to spit some truth ya'll so listen up. Go to class; engaging in discussion actually does help study for the midterm. Memorize lists (3 things min.), and don't study the night before, her MCQ is tricky -- it's the details that count. Make sure you study the slides and leave time for review at the end. Overall good lecturer, &knowledgeable

Very difficult Multiple choice questions, but fair short answers. Do the readings aside from the lectures because she tests you on them. The midterm is worth as much as the final exam so do well on it.
Very difficult multiple choice questions but fairly easy short answers, do the readings even though they seem irrelevant. I would recommend the other prof who teaches this course.
Great prof, very helpful! Fair midterms and final, if you put effort into the course youll recieve the mark you want.
Best teacher ever! Take one of her classes if you get the chance!!

Excellent prof. The exams are difficult but if you study well you will be ok. I don't agree with her class being boring or falling asleep. I think the people that wrote those messages are people that don't study and don't have a proper sleeping pattern. This prof is really an asset for the school. :)

I took many courses with Karen. But I believe this one is the icing on the cake. She's an awesome instructor with a big heart and a big interest in both her subject matter and her students. If you have problems she'll go the extra mile to help you out. Would definitely recommend her to any of my fellow colleagues.

excellent prof! teaches everything very well, provides useful slideshows and videos, text is useful. Course material is hard, so tests are hard, but are what you are taught in class. FAir tests! you get the grade you earn

She's a great teacher: im sure she reads comments about her here because now she's using a lot of videos and anecdotes which make the classes fun and interesting... i found the exam harder that what i expected but it's doable.. (if you have studied)
i really enjoy her she teachs hard classes but the exams are very doable with that material

definitely knows what she's talking about. She's monotone and can make you fall asleep, but shes fantastic. her slides are very detailed, but all the info is right there in the slide, which is awesome because you dont need the text book! If you thought hss2101 was hard, your in for a surprise. Just put in the time and effort and you'll be fine :D

very boring, very monotone, HUGE amount of VERY specific things you have to brute force  memorize.  i'm sure she's a nice person, but as a prof... eh, nah.  agree with comments about falling asleep.  slides usually make sense for the first 10 or so, then it quickly breaks down into a wall-o-text of random 3 letter and 4 letter acronyms.
Awesome lady and just a great professor! She really knows her stuff!

Dr.Phillips is an extremely nice person and takes the time to create detailed and knowledge-packed slides which help her students study. this promotes students getting high grades. i think people overlook how much effort it takes to put a class together and she clearly puts in lots of time and energy.

She is awesome. Her classes can get boreing becuase she doesn't deviate from the slides much, but overall I fnd that you learn in the lectures. By far her biggest strength is answering questions, if you don't understand something ask her. Midterm was exactly what she said it would be, a lot to know and specific. The final caught me by suprise.

Overall this class was OK. Before the final was actually pretty easy if you put in a moderate amount of work, but the final took me by surprise :S. Somewhat interesting material but it gets quite difficult to remember all of the molecules' involvement in different pathways/reactions. Midterm was a breeze compared to the final though, so heads up :P
Ms. Phillips is very knowledgable, didn't like the number of slides but besides that the class was great.  I would definately recommend this class to anyone
I really enjoyed her class she made everything every interesting and easy to learn if you pay attention and put in a little work.
She was very helpful and very knowledgable

Karen really seemed to come into her own when teaching this class. I've had her for other classes, but I didn't relly enjoy having her as a teacher then. The midterm and assignments were easy (no final). The final project however, was the biggest task I've ever undertaken. Planning a health care program by myself was too much.
AMAZING COURSE! Midterms and evaluations are straight forward and very fair.
Worst Prof ever.  She is boring and marks extremely inconsitent.  The ONLY good thing about her class is that there is no need to buy the text book.
Maybe the lectures are boring, but Dr Phillips is actually really nice. Go and see her during office hours, she's awesome!

Oh Karen...a competent professor for a change who knows what she's talking about but she needs to step it up a bit in the lectures. I've fallen asleep in about 3/4 of them. It's just ssoooo boing. Her voice is monotone and she's reads from the slides. Little to zero interaction with the class and no stories or examples to make things interesting.
thus far the class rocks

dear phillips : I already know how to read - SO STOP READING TO ME & TEACH ME!!!! If you enjoy having an entire text book read to you , this class is for you. Though you will have to re-read it all again because i bet you $100 dollars you will only go to the first class or you will fall asleep, whichever comes first. good luck and sweet dreams

BEND OVER BECAUSE YOU"LL GET IT IN THE ASS! If you ever take this class forget buying the book since it's typed out on the power point slides. It is as boring as hell listening to her read her slides for the entire class. Inflection in her voice... i think not!

There was just way too much information and the exams asked questions that were way too specific.  Maybe 2 midterms would help make things easier...and it was brutal making it through classes without falling asleep.

The material itself is very interesting, but i am very disappointed in how much material we are required to remember. The total workload for the final was ridiculous. Most of the students i spoke to didnt finish studying. I would like Professory Phillips to consider this for the next year.
love the class!
